One of the best Kao Soy in Chiangmai. I don't recommend the underground mushroom dish as it has a very pungent smell and weird experience eating it but everything else was great!

The place is really pretty and nice to sit, however the food wasn‚Äôt that good. I‚Äôve had khao soi before and this wasn‚Äôt nearly as good, the food was a bit cold and we got some skewers that tasted good but the meat was very tough. I wouldn‚Äôt return, specially being in Thailand there are way better places.
Best bowl of Khao soi you can find on nimman, went here multiple times, no regrets!

One of the best kao soy in Chiang Mai. Was on the Michelin guide in 2020/21. Gets pretty crowded during lunch and dinner time so best go a little early. Otherwise there‚Äôs a bit of a wait but it‚Äôs not long. The beef kao soi is very good and the portion is just right so that you can order other items too. Well worth the trip down to try this.
The favor of dishes is absolutely awesome, however, you have to experience many flies if you sitting outdoor

Absolutely delicious! Our first Khao Soi: we got the stewed beef (tender and yummy), and the northern pork sausage (fantastic with quite a kick to it, not good if you don't like spicy food!). The combination of the flavourful sauce with the two noodle textures was great. Recommend to anyone.

The khao soi here lives up to the hype! My friend took me here, and I was unaware of its reputation. The beef khao soi was my personal favorite, it's so tender and mixes perfectly with the curry. The service is quick and efficient. I really like the button at each table that allows you to call a waiter when you're ready. Our food was served just a few minutes after ordering. As a note, it does seem to get pretty busy on weekends and holidays. If you want to avoid a wait, I'd recommend an early lunch on a weekday.
Khao Soi is amazing. The beef is tender and the curry sauce is savoury. However, the dessert is disappointing. The coconut milk used is expired with a weird taste. Just order Khao Soi.

There are many types of topping on the Kao Soy menu that you will never found in ordinary restaurants. The taste is very amazing. This is one of the most delicious Kao Soy I‚Äôve ever had. Appetizers are also great. I really recommend ‚ÄúKai Satay‚Äù and local food set. Staff is polite. Service is also quick. There are many tables and seats so you don‚Äôt have to wait for long time.

I‚Äôve been living in Chiang Mai for eight years and it‚Äôs the first time I‚Äôve come to this restaurant. The Kao Soy chicken was quite a tasty dish, balanced, and to be expected for very good northern Thai food. And if you live in Chiangmai or you‚Äôre passing through definitely worth coming here to try the local cuisine.

I came to Khao Soy Nimman in March and it was close. So I am so happy today I can eat this delicious food. I never had seafood Khao Soi in Bangkok. It‚Äôs first time try seafood and chicken Khao Soi. üòãüòãüëçüèªüëçüèª

Came with my friend but ordered curry mee and spring roll only. When they served the food, they gave us two sets of cutlery without request. The staffs really offered a good service. The food also not bad definitely deserve five stars from us.

This restaurant appears to be famous among tourists, I came around 11:30 and was lucky to get inside before people came and started the long line waiting. The Khao Soy is just okay the noodles a bit hard for my taste. The spring rolls are surprisingly better than I expected. The dishes seemed not spicy compared to other places. Also I like the bowl they use for drinks, didn't see anywhere else in Chiangmai. So I think Kao Soy Nimman is a nice option for those who want to try local foods that are adjusted to tourists taste, the location is also a plus, well located close to Onenimman.

Checked out Kao Soy Nimman, a spot that's got a nod from Michelin, so you know it's got some serious creds. True to the hype, the place was packed, with a no-reservations policy meaning you grab a number and hang tight for your turn. Dropped by on a weekday, post-lunch rush around 2pm, and still clocked a 40-minute wait. Went straight for their namesake dish, the Kao Soy. Pretty tasty, though it leaned towards the saltier side - flavor lovers would be into it. The chicken BBQ was alright, nothing to write home about. Price-wise, it's a winner, and the vibe of the restaurant is pretty chill, albeit super busy. They could do with a few more hands on deck, as getting the bill took a bit of effort and a couple of reminders. Was the wait worth it? Depends on your mood and schedule. If you're looking to kill some time and escape the heat, it's not a bad option. But if you're not up for the wait, maybe swing by during off-peak hours.

I ordered Khao Soi beef , chicken skewers and the dessert The beef was a bit tough and not as tender as expected and the gravy is rather thick and Smokey . Definitely worth a try for anyone who is seeking for a different taste of khao soi in Chiang mai but it isn‚Äôt my personal favourite overall However the red chestnut dessert is rather mind blowing ! The chicken skewers is good , loving the nutty sauce and the juiciness and tenderness of the chicken .

Good khao soi, but for the price I expected better: it could be fresher and the flavors more distinct. It didn't look much like the pictures. One sitting area looks nice, but they sat me in a side area that had no ambiance whatsoever. The food came out very quickly.
Portions are a little on the small size but the flavour was excellent

Their main dish, Khao soi is the best I've ever tried. Hang le a little bit strange but also delicious. Special coconut drink was great. Reasonable prices and both air-conditioned and outdoor tables are available. This place is very popular and gets busy at times.

Large selection of northern Thai dishes and more versions of Khao Soi than I‚Äôve seen anywhere. Taste was decent although not amazing. Prices are slightly high for the type of food but, then, this is a tourist area. Good job of sticking with the Lanna theme.

I had to try the northern dish Khao Soi, while in Chiang Mai. We had walked past the restaurant, the day before and it was packed. We came back and were very pleased with the dish. My wife had the option with chicken leg, and I the fried pork. There is seating both inside and outside. The chili paste was also excellent.

For Khao Soi with fried pork. The soup is normal. I did not find the special from its taste. The crispy yellow noodles is hard, I put soup into it and waited for a while. The fried pork is very sticky, given just a very very few vegetables (so stinky! ) . Another side dish is fried dumplings, this one is good and nice smell of herbs. The outdoor area have a lot of mosquitoes, the staffs seem to know about this issue but ignorance. So overall, do not recommend.
We tried Khao Soi with seafood it was really delicious! PS: it's a famous restaurant, we had to queue to get a table but it was fast and the service was great!
Very delicious food and interesting menu!

Was here before 10am, hence no q when they started serve. Service and atmosphere is good. Ordered The curry noodles topping with fried crispy noodles & chicken leg / fried pork. Too much fried crispy noodles, not really able to soak the curry, don't feel really match the taste. The curry noodles somehow overated. Very oily and lack of aroma of curry. Maybe this is the taste of khao soi...XD

Recommended!!!! I like Kao Soy here. It‚Äôs just a little bit spicy so it‚Äôs easy to eat. So many toppings available for us to choose. The drinks and desserts menu are also interesting. I tried super bowl which I think it‚Äôs a lot for me. I like Khai Satay too. It‚Äôs impressive visiting there. I would recommend you all to try.

We were craving for Kao Soy and we found this on Google Maps, never noticed this is a Michelin Restaurant until we reached there then only we knew. I think it's because of peak hour, the staff are all busy to approach us, so we kind of wait for some time for the table and also ordering. We ordered two different types of Kao Soy, the taste is okay but doesn't taste any spicy, we are not sure what the taste is supposed to be because this is our first time having Kao Soy üòÑ Not to mention, the dessert can taste the ice from the icebox üòÇ Again, we are not sure if that is 'normal' tastes? Overall it is okay, will try the other Kao Soy restaurant in future.

This was a Michelin guide 2020 restaurant recommended to us from a Chiang Mai local. We waited a good 30 minutes but they churn people through the restaurant pretty quickly. The khao soi was absolutely delicious. I got the pork belly Khao soi and the pork belly melts in your mouth. The soup base had lots of herbs and spices with a little bit of curry based influenced. My favorite part was how the noodles were both crispy and soft. Soft for the parts in the soup and crispy for the pieces above it. I loved that combination of textures in this dish. We also got some delicious sides, calamari, chicken satay, and dumplings. All very good. So overall it was totally worth the wait and the prices are fair. Would 100% recommend going here.
We were advised to eat here by our grab driver in order to try Kao Soy (typical food from Northern Thailand). It was super good and the atmosphere is also very local with few tourists. We loved it!

This wasn't the best Khao Soi I've had in Chiang Mai; the broth seemed a bit bland. The prices here are quite high compared to other places but if you want to try a place on the Michelin guide you pay the price. They charge you for a bowl of ice about 20 baht. Very famous among tourists and can be crowded during lunch. We had to wait in a queue for about 40 mins. Besides the signature Khao Soi, we ordered several side dishes. The crispy pork skewers tasted quite good but not crispy, we had the mango sticky rice, the portion is huge but taste was just average. However, the dining environment is nice. This place is quite famous, but I think it's overrated.

Loved their khao soi dish! It was my first time but it was excellent choice to visit this restaurant. Very comfortable settings and friendly staff! Came here twice during my stay in Chiang Mai and never disappointed! No wonder why it is listed in Michelin 2020 & 2021!

This place is a little pricy for Kao Soy but the food is wonderful and a great place to take your guests for experiencing local Kao Soy flavors and atmosphere. I wish they had an option of the bigger portion for all Kao Soys but only for house special. Floor staff were well trained and always were checking each table.

Came for early dinner Ordered two curry noodle, fried spring roll, egg omelette and stir fry vegetable. 1) staff got distracted while taking order, client need to repeat few times. No smile on every staff. 2) apart from the small portion of those noodle, those fried food (spring roll and Omelett) were ruined by the think powder. Overall, super low CP value and not worth for Michelin.

I would say the stewed beef Kao Soy was delicious as was the pork but the beef had a much better flavor. The pork kao soy could have used another scoop of broth. Initial arrival was a bit clumsy as they were very busy. Only got one menu but worked through that. Took a few minutes to get waited on but after that the food and the appetizers came out real fast. I would recommend this place if you want to try some Kao Soy. The prices were pretty reasonable for what we ordered.
Recommend khao soy, the sausage and fermented pork. Sausage can be quite spicy but worth a try. Fermented pork was quite an interested but a very local dish to Chiang Mai

Kao Soy Nimman is one of the uniqueness place serving Khao Soi with plenty of meat to add on for topping. Not only the Khao Soi availble here, they also served the Northern Thai‚Äôs dishes and Thai sweet. The bow of Khao Soi is good with the light soup but intense in aroma of curry paste, the soup is quite sweet not to spicy even adding some chili to it. Khao Soi noodle a bit soft not to tender, deep fried noodle is not crispy. Chicken is tender and hard but the beef is fine. The herbal drinks and Thai sweet are recommended here, very amazing. This is a good place to enjoy the Northern Thai food, if you getting bored of Khao Soi.

I went there bcs I was in the area and they got michelin so I thought "Why don't just try it?". No waiting line at around 2.30 PM. The service is quite nice and fast. I tried Kao Soy with chicken, the soup and fried noodle was so good but I think the chicken was so so. You can try if there's no line, but you can also find another Kao Soy in the whole city

Totally blown away by the goodness served in the bowl. Amazing varieties pf the khao soy - so there‚Äôs something for everyone here. Please do try the traditional drinks served over soda cans! Must have place if you are in chiang mai ‚ù§Ô∏èü•∞üòçüòä
I love this place! khao soy with various toppings, also the bamboo worms are nice
Curry noodles dishes are outstanding. The egg rolls are light, crisp, and fresh. Coconut and butterfly flower drinks hit the spot. We'll be back to try other items on the menu.
Incredible taste of Rice noodles with spicy pork sauce!! Northern Thai curry noodle with beef was also nice. But the noodle is quite too thick. Very good and quick service. Price was reasonable.
Loved this place, great ambience and very very tasty food. A must visit when you are in Chiang Mai. I ordered kao soy, tom yum soup (shrimp), fried chicken, coconut water and a dessert.

Not a good experience. We are in Chiang Mai in Nimman district for quite some time and only now we went to Kao Soy for the first time. First weird thing is that they close already at 8pm and we were rushed to leave the place as we arrived just after 7pm for s dinner. The searing was very uncomfortable and the service was not very attentive, we had to wave at the waiter multiple times so they finally notice us and we can order the food. The food was probably worst I had in any restaurant in Chiang Mai, maybe we just picked wrong but out of three meals, every one of them was not tasteful at all. The noodles which were supposed to be non spicy were spicy as hell. Not sure, maybe we just picked a wrong day and everything went badly for us.
I didn‚Äôt like the texture of the noddles compared to other ones I had around, but the soup is not that spicy. Overall, I think I would order if I don‚Äôt know what to eat.

Kao Soy Nimman is a popular restaurant located in the trendy Nimman area of Chiang Mai. The restaurant specializes in Kao Soy, a traditional northern Thai dish that consists of a rich and flavorful curry broth served with tender chicken or beef and crispy noodles. The restaurant's cozy ambiance and friendly service make it a great spot for a casual meal with friends or family. In addition to Kao Soy, the menu also features a variety of other northern Thai dishes, as well as some international options. Overall, Kao Soy Nimman is a great place to enjoy some delicious northern Thai cuisine in a relaxed setting.

Good taste, small portion ( two or three bites) , overcrowded and overpriced, Waiting for 30 min- 1h to be served Don‚Äôt park on the narrow street, as ur car will block the street and got fine and locked by the police. There is a parking lot nearby charged 50 baht, which is easy to find

This is a restaurant mainly for tourists, and the price level is more expensive than other Thai restaurants that sell similar kind of foods. The quality of the dishes and other things such as atmosphere, service etc. are all good.

Authentic Northern Thai cuisine. Must try the Kao Soy! There‚Äôs always a long queue but it moves quite quickly; we were given a table after waiting for less than 10min. Food was amazing and service was quick too. Highly recommend visiting this place if you are in Chiang Mai!

We had the Khao Soy Kai Jaew and it was simply delicious! We don't understand the negative reviews about the price, as we thought it was fair for the excellent quality and quantity of the food. An incredible gastronomic experience in Chiang Mai that we highly recommend!

The best Kao Soi I've had by far. The food and atmosphere of the restaurant is exceptional But more importantly the staff are incredible. I forgot to take my change and left in a rush. I came back and the staff were incredible honest and helpful. Great business, makes me want to come back. Super grateful!
a must-go restaurant. I can wait in line. It's so delicious. The doughnut shop next door is soft and delicious, so please try it.
Nice curry! The spring roll is great!

Cool vibes and Great local dish! We ended up with the super bowl with all the fixings. It was great! We also ordered some of their juices. Great presentation on the drinks. See the attached pictures! It's pricier than buying it with street food, but that's how it goes in most restaurants in nimman.
Their dishes are small in portions but very delicious. If you are going for mango sticky rice ask in advance to keep one for you :) Chicken satay were okay..

i‚Äôm not sure why it‚Äôs so highly rated and packed with long lines? the khao soi is not amazing, just decent and more on the sweet side. my biggest gripe is the tiny portions of the noodles - esp for what you‚Äôre paying. no chilis to add. toppings were fine. a bit overrated i think.

Went here again and again during our month in Chiang Mai. Lots of variety for khao soi protein, from Thai sausage, to shrimp, pork loin, and omelette to name a few. We tried the laab, spring rolls, and tempura shrimp appetizers as well. All were ok, but the khao soi is the star!
Service is fast and clean. The food taste that I did order is quite too spicy. The soup taste spicy, oily, creamy, herbal, a bit sour (put some lime). The herb drink is quite expensive and sweet.

It‚Äôs the quality of ingredients that nowhere else can beat. The spices and fresh ingredients are all sourced locally. You can taste the heart and efforts the owner put in to make the best of the best. You pay for what you get. Honest opinion: better than the ‚Äúbest‚Äù one.

What a disappointment! The Kao Soi I had ordered wasn't available, so I opted for the shrimp one. The shrimps looked like they came straight from the refrigerator. The dish was very small and testless. Overall, it's very expensive for what it is. The Michelin years are long gone

A place you must drop by when you in Chiang Mai. The star of the shop is the curry noddle! Come with various type of dishes including beef, chicken, pork, seafood and vege only option is available too! Saw they also receive Michelin awards for both 2020 and 2021 as well. The curry broth is the soul and you shall go with the super bowl option if you want to fill up your belly with all the curry noodleüòÅ else the normal one is perfect since we are all here to taste as much as food as we canü§ì highly recommendedü¶ã PS: remember to get a queue number from the service crew if you seen ppl waiting outside the reception area :)
great atmosphere and delicious food. beef kao soy 7.8/10
Ate indoors on a hot day. AC was good, khao soi was great! It‚Äôs a bit on the lighter side than other khao sois I‚Äôve had in the past but it was a refreshing change. Beef was super tender!

This is one of the best places for Khao Soi. They make their own special yellow noodle served Al dente. Nam Prik Noom tastes excellent but spicy. People with low spice tolerance be warned. Love their special drinks especially their coconut that can be eaten as a whole. Good and quick service. The queue was long but the turnover is quick. Recommended Foods: Any Khao Soi (if you have huge appetite, go for Super Khao Soi), Mixed Appetizer Platter ‡∏≠‡∏≠‡πÄ‡∏î‡∏¥‡∏£‡πå‡∏ü‡πÄ‡∏°‡∏∑‡∏≠‡∏á, Khang Hed Torp (‡πÅ‡∏Å‡∏á‡πÄ‡∏´‡πá‡∏î‡∏ñ‡∏≠‡∏ö)

This place is a culinary gem! Their authentic and flavorful Northern Thai khao soi is a must-try, bursting with aromatic spices and tender meat. The cosy ambience and friendly service make it a delightful dining experience. A top-notch spot for foodies!
The soup was only lukewarm, and the meat was almost cold and felt undercooked. The spring rolls and vegetables we ordered was okay. Overall very dissapointing

I arrived at 7:30pm on a lunar new year day and queued for 30 mins to get a table, but the wait was totally worth it. The khao soy was a delight - it‚Äôs so flavorful with so much texture to it. Also ordered a pork belly and a curry rice noddle. All dishes are an explosion of flavors and at very reasonable prices. I was still dreaming about the khao soy when I woke up the next day.

amazing khao soi, super refreshing drinks (especially the grass jelly), and delicious mango sticky rice! dined here twice during my short visit and was not disappointed. you may have to flag down a server to place an order and get your check. they were quite busy!
The beef noodle worth to try, beef so tender. Beef itself make the khao soy taste great. Recommend to order this instead others. Its hard to find parking around this area so better be prepared.

This place was packed when I arrived. There was a wait outside and you have to grab a number from the guy that works there. Even so I waited maybe 10 minutes tops and it was so worth it. Food and service were amazing. üëçüëç

Not sure why this place was rated as popular. Service was horrible. After was seated, we wondered if we had to walk to a place to ask for menu. We had to flag one of the many service people around to get the menus. Waited another 10 minutes, flagged down a service person, so we could order foods. Same when we wanted more beers. After 15m12s, we received foods. Khao Soi was okay. Pork curry did not taste curry, was full of fat. Never tasted curry that bad in Thailand. This place would not be my choice again in the future.

Various northern cuisine. They not just serve Khaosoy but also have other northern dishes. The place is clean and neat with the northern deco style. Giving you warm and cozy vibe. Mix customers both Thai and tourists. Presentation of the foods are good and tasty. Price is alright for what you getting.

Conveniently located in famous Nimman Street. This northern style cuisine offers variety of dishes that garantee you will leave Chaingmai with satisfaction of northern food craving. However I personally would loved that some dishes to be more authentic taste rather than adapted for foreigners tastes.

BEWARE!! I had horrendous food poisoning from Kao Soy Nimman that lasted three days. I hadn‚Äôt eaten anything else prior or after visiting so it was without doubt from here. I ordered the beef khao soi and chicken satay as a side. It was very busy when I visited so must be a serious issue with food preparation or storage in the kitchen. Usually I would assume a busy restaurant with high turnover would be safe. Certainly not in this case!!
My first taste of khao soi and I liked the raw red onions the most. The flavour of the broth was ok but didn‚Äôt stand out for the price charged.

Hmm, what can I say, I‚Äôm not a big fan of khao soy. In fact this is only my second time trying it (after a span of 10 years apart) and I still don‚Äôt like it. Luckily the side dishes (northern thai sausage & egg plant salad) are good. Perhaps not for me but those who love khao soy may hv s different view.

Arrived when it was dinner service and there was a queuing ticket system whereby you are given a number and wait to be called, got in within 10 mins Staffs are friendly and definitely able accommodate to different visiting tourists. Kao Soy is their signature dish with different meat options available; portion is alright if you are also ordering multiple side dishes Moo Bping was also recommended on the menu; different from the ones I‚Äôve known. This is more on the savoury side with a chewier texture [Take Note] Moo Bping takes awhile to be served which they don‚Äôt inform beforehand, around 20 mins If you do not have the patience, order something else and don‚Äôt shout at service staffsüòä
Very good food, guys. Khao Soy is a must try when visiting Chaing Mai. This is a very good place to do so. ‚ú®Ô∏è
The That tea needed to pay first tastes great. Balanced flavor. Other dishes are just fine. I would recommend other places.

Ordered "northern style spicy minced pork salad wrapped in crispy wontons" - they tasted pretty good but there were big chunks of blood cubes, intestines etc in there which I'm not really accustomed to as a westerner, I kind of expected just pork mince meat as opposed to alot of organs.. I also ordered the "northern style pork curry made with peanuts, garlic and ginger" which tasted ok but was quite mild flavoured and watery + half of the curry was fat and skin (again I kind of expected just pork meat - as shown in the picture in their menu). Considering this wasn't a cheap meal, I was overall disappointed in the quality. To make matters worse, I ordered delivery to my hotel and was sent no cutlery so I had to run around to 7-11 to ask for a tiny plastic spoon, made for stirring coffee". Food was cold by the time I got round to opening it up. Dont think i'll be ordering from this place again!

Really delicious Khao Soi. I ordered the Thai sausage Khao Soi for a change and it was really delicious! Great depth of flavour and the perfect level of spice. 99 baht for chicken Khao Soi and 125 Baht for the Thai sausage Khao Soi. We also tried the chicken satay to start but I've had a lot better elsewhere

I got the pork option, 90 baht. I was surprised to find out water is 20 baht. Personally the broth was too greasy and sweet for my taste. However the pork was cooked very nicely. I also liked the shelled coconut that my friend ordered. It‚Äôs definitely pricey compared to local khao soi which is around 50 baht. I would go to a smaller restaurant so you don‚Äôt have to wait.

They have many staffs but the speed of serving food is quite slow. The Kao Soy is good but beware when you are choosing what kind of ingredients to match. My friend ordered mushrooms Kao Soy and the mushroom doesn't taste so good if compare to pork or egg. Their crispy pork is really good.
It‚Äôs an authentic Chiangmai food. All the dishes can not be complain, very very delicious. For 7 persons, we spend 1900 baht.
Have been in Thailand for a few days and this is the only restaurant that disappointed me. We ordered the signature needle and a few other dishes. Doesn‚Äôt taste good.

My favorite Khao Soi place in Nimman area! I come here multiple times per Thailand trip. The Khao Soi is both delicious and inexpensive. Ambiance is nice too, and service is excellent. I can see why they‚Äôre on the Michelin guide.

Plenty of waiters and waitresses and very polite. The food portion may be somewhat small and spicy for westerners but not too pricey. The taste was nice for non-local Thais yet OK for the locals. There were kinds of Thai dessert available. Recommend for a bit early or late meal time to avoid the long line. Parking was limited to sideways. It was nice to try. Recommended.
Rewriting my previous review. Come back to this restaurant after 2 years and the quality is still consistently delicious. There are improvements in organizing the queue and cleaner toilet.

We hit this place up for lunch after hiking the Monk‚Äôs trail to Wat Pha Lat and Wat Phra Doi Suthrep and it hit the spot. I liked the open outdoor seating. They also had an easy selection of dishes that were mild enough for our kids. We did the pork and the beef kao soy and I liked the pork a little better but both were fantastic.
Went into Kai soy and ordered up almost half the menu. It was amazing. I would definitely recommend this place and come back again next time I‚Äôm in Chiang Mai.
The greatest place in Chiangmai. If you haven‚Äôt been here, than you haven‚Äôt arrived yet. Best KaoSoy ever. Best ingredients and fast service. Really worth every time!

Their Kao soi is a delicious curry soup with firm noodles and crispy noodles on top. The chicken I had was succulently flavoursome, and paired well with the crispy fried noodles on top. We waited around 40min when we came on a Wednesday lunchtime (12:30 ish). But towards 13:30 it‚Äôs not as busy
My favourite restaurant in the world. Super fast service. Amazingly tasty Kao Soy. Great ambience. Can‚Äôt wait to return.

Hardly waited although there was a queue because I said OK to a bar seating. I didn't know it was in the sun though (shaded somewhat by plants), to be fair it wasn't too hot. Do not try their signature dishes and opted of something different. The fried pork with garlic saved this review for them. Was not too impressed with the offerings, but may return for a second round to try other dishes to see what the locals are queuing up for (Michellin star noodle dish)
I have tried Khaosoy with beef which one not much spicy since I checked with them just little bit spicy one for me and Mango stricky rice then. Both of them are nice, I enjoyed. You must try it!
There was a line. There were 20 people in front of us. In general, everything is fine. The guys are good, they clean and take out the dishes when they are ready. Kao Soy was great!
Their Kao Soy was quite good but a bit pricey, other dishes were so-so. And all seemed salty for my own taste. The dessert was pretty disappointing though.
Great tastes and a good spot to try a variety of the northern foods. Has an AC spot towards the inside area.

Got the pork noodles. Taste was delicious. Pork was cooked well. Noodles perfect texture. 90thb Nice setting and very fast service. Had the meal out within a few minutes. Did not order anything else but they have a sizeable menu of northern Thai dishes at reasonable prices.

One of my favourite places to have a decent Kao Soi and very nice Chiang Mai Sausage! They have a good variety of the most famous dish and everything tastes just amazingly good! The location is quiet and nice, the staff super friendly and service superb! A must try for everyone who is on love with this tasty dish like me ü•∞

The food was so good, very tasty. The staff is friendly. They serve the food really fast. There‚Äôs a button on the table you need to press to call for service to place your order or to pay. We came on a Wednesday night without any reservation.
Best kai soy and dessert we had in Chiang Mai , portion are generous and price is acceptable

Kao Soy Nimman is a must visit if you want to try khao soi! They have loads of different khao soi‚Äôs to choose from as well as other dishes and desserts. We ordered the khao soi with chicken and pork, both were full of flavor and tasted delicious. They were both a little spicy but it was not too bad with a nice cold drink on the side. We finished our lunch with mango sticky rice.
Super tasty noodles, service was quick and good. But we ordered a northern Thailand spicy herbal chicken soup, thought it was going to be a safe choice but turn pretty funky lol

Place is beautiful and opened, servers understands English well, price is good, taste wonderful and spicy. Portion of Kao soi is questionably small, some menu (for us it was green curry) took a while to get. Overall great experience. Expect to wait in line.

ÈÇì‰∏ΩÂêõ‚Äôs favorite restaurant, as they said. So I didn‚Äôt expect much about the food when I went there. But it turned out unexpectedly tasty and special!!! The super bowl curry noodle is a must order!!! Side dishes are also surprisingly good (try out the raw pork if you don‚Äôt mind)!

In a city full of the best soup in the world (sorry, Ramen: you‚Äôre a fine mistress, but...) this place has the NoThai specialty dialed IN!! There‚Äôs a vast menu covering a ton of options for Kao Soy and even a great vegetarian bowl. The sides were good as well. It‚Äôs pricier than other places and all-our extravagant compared to the street food, but it was mostly a trendy local spot, so that made sense. So delish!
Great Khao soi, good location. There was a queue, but waiting was not too long.
one of the best khao soi u could get in chaingmai. soups are slightly flavourful than the other places.
Excellent meal. The khao soi soup is fragrant and the egg noodles are bouncy. The chicken satay was surprisingly tender and flavorful‚Äîwould recommend.
Best Kao Soy I‚Äôve ever had! Food, service, and ambience are all 5 stars. This is a must try! We also got satay and tempura shrimp - all very tasty.

I think it‚Äôs definitely overrated to me. Long queue but proper seating arrangement. I find Khao Soy Mae Sai is still the right choice! Tender chicken, tasty gravy, better seasoned vegetable! And Mae Sai cost only 50baht per bowl! Read my review on them!

Kao Soy Nimman, located in Chiang Mai‚Äôs trendy Nimman area, is renowned for its rich and flavorful Khao Soi, a Northern Thai coconut curry noodle soup. The restaurant offers a variety of protein options, including chicken, beef, pork, seafood, and Chiang Mai sausage, allowing diners to customize their bowls. The broth is praised for its depth and balance, combining creamy coconut milk with aromatic spices, and the noodles are perfectly cooked, complemented by crispy fried noodles on top. In addition to Khao Soi, the menu features other Northern Thai specialties and refreshing herbal drinks like gardenia and pennywort.

The khao soi here is served in a porcelain bowl with the pickle, onion and lime wedge in a separate metal dish. I went past the kitchen and noticed a big vat of curry boiling away on the stove so it doesn't make sense that it's merely warm. This review might seem spiteful, but I truly had a very poor experience here that is likely to be reflective of the general quality of the restaurant. Kao Soy Nimman is a Michelin bib gourmand place which has definitely earned it much fame among tourists. We had to line up for about 30 minutes before being given a table, which isn‚Äôt a problem in itself. However, ONCE we got inside and placed our orders (one bowl of khao soi and one omelette), it took 40 minutes before the khao soi arrived. We made several requests to the staff about where our food was, but no one ever seemed to be able to definitively help. The khao soi took 40 minutes to arrive, but we waited about 70 minutes for the omelette and it never came. We ultimately decided we had spent too long in the restaurant, asked the waitress if we could cancel our omelette request (to which she kindly said yes), paid up and left. As for the khao soi, it was extremely bland and watered down, and the meat was tough and chewy. I have since eaten at Khao Soi Maesai and Khao Soi Lung Prakit Kad Kom (both Michelin bib gourmand places too), and their khao soi was incomparably better and the quality of the meat was far superior too. Not to mention, the prices at this restaurant are 3x those at the other two, but for what reason? This isn‚Äôt an agenda-driven review by any means, but simply an honest reflection of what I experienced. I hope it is helpful, especially to those of you who are considering visiting on a tight time schedule - you will not miss anything important by skipping this place.

There were plenty of empty tables available, at least 4 (refer to my photos), when we arrived, but we weren‚Äôt seated until 20 mins later which shows they just aren‚Äôt very efficient with managing things. Also, there were 4-5 employees wearing orange shirts whose job is to take orders from customers (you can‚Äôt scan a QR code to order by yourself) but only 1-2 of them were working and the other employees were just slacking off. So when I gestured to have my order taken, one of them would look at another, expecting their colleague to take responsibility and that repeated a few times, and so I had to wait a few minutes to even have someone come over and take our order. Also, their queuing system is not clear at all. There should a sign at the entrance that clearly states that you need to collect a blue ticket from one of their employees. Overall, I thought the food was quite average and not worth what you pay for (a bill for 2 came to 525 baht, and the service wasn‚Äôt great, and you will most likely have to queue to eat here, and so I definitely would say it‚Äôs not worth your time and energy to eat such average food.
Taste was ok. Very foreigner like. Doesn‚Äôt have much chilli. Have to order extra. Most of the food doesn‚Äôt include the actual chilli. Foreigner taste. But the taste is still ok
Truly authentic and highly recommended. great flavours and great value.
Nice atmosphere, good food, super clean and nice pleasant staff Congrats

Delicious kao soi ! Spicy level is fair enough. service is good , the place is clean. Crowded but that‚Äôs ok. It‚Äôs worth it. A bit expensive compared to other Michelin rewarded kao soi restaurants. However this one is more tasty , less spicy and more clean.
Not a place to go for original Khao soi. The taste is suitable for tourists who cannot bear real spiciness of Thai food. All is acceptable but the soft noodle that is much thicker than average.

My husband loves khao soi, so we were on the hunt for the best khao soi in town, and saw the great reviews on this place! Although not the best khao soi, it was pretty delicious! When we got there around lunch time, there was a huge line up! We contemplated waiting or not, but ultimately decided to since we were there anyways and we really wanted to try this place out. We got our number from the hostess and she told us there were 20 numbers ahead of us so we were prepared to wait for at least an hour. There is a bubble tea place right beside it so we ordered a bubble tea while we waited. To our surprise, the wait only took about 25 minutes! We got seated in the air-conditioned space at the back, which was good because it was such a hot day out! I ordered the chicken khao soi, my husband ordered the beef khao soi, and we also got the crispy wontons and steamed vegetables to share. The food came within 10 minutes, which was very reasonable. The khao soi tasted quite good, just the right amount of richness, and not too spicy. Since this place is so popular among tourists, we felt that perhaps the dish was not truly authentic, compared to some other khao soi we have tried. Delicious food nonetheless! The food was definitely tourist pricing since it was pricier than most other local restaurants, but we expected that going in so no surprises there. I would definitely return to this place if I find myself in Chiang Mai again, but I‚Äôd probably try to go a bit earlier to avoid the lunch time rush.

Beautiful setting with decent khao Soi. My favorite part about Khao Soi Nimman is the variety of proteins to choose from. Fair warning: this place can get pretty crowded with selfie-taking tourists. Especially during the lunch hour.
Kao Soy was not my cup of tea, however Kao Soy at this place was an exception. It tastes amazing, rich in flavor, not too spicy and not too salty.

Curry noodle is nice the gravy is nice a bit like watery Mee Rebus gravy but more spicy. The bamboo shoots soup is actually more spicy and nice beware of fish bone though. The desert is a pass too normal.
SImply a good Khao soi restaurant. Sometimes simplicity is better than complexity.

After previously visiting this restaurant 7 years ago, we were excited to see that it still exists and the Khao Soi is still as delicious as ever! Come a little earlier to avoid a long wait, as it gets busy in the evening. If there is a line, it moves pretty fast and definitely worth the wait!
Delicious Khao Soi but very small portions. Don't bother with the iced desserts, it is mostly ice cubes.
One of my boyfriend and I top spot for Khaosoi in Chiang Mai. Chicken khaosoi is our fav, very very tender chicken and creamy broth! I always bring my international friends here and they love it!
Large variety of dishes. Delicious food. Well priced. They have these buttons to call your waiter. They respond instantly.

Don‚Äôt feel like it is worth the price. Portion is small, the Khao soi is tasty but not really mind-blowing.. if you want to have a nice ambience and try other dishes too then maybe this place would be okay. It is also open later than the other famous places for Khao Soi. Seems to cater a lot to Chinese tourists - waitress could speak mandarin
Delicious and variety of Khao Soi - Northern style curry noodle. Location right in the middle of Nimman area , easy to get around.
Very nice and traditional northern Thai cuisine presented in a new modern way. You should come try if you are around Nimman area.
The place was just amazing , clean and quiet. The staff was more than welcoming. The fooood was just a next level ‚ù§Ô∏è

What a great place! But forget the place, the FOOD IS AWESOME! It's our first Kao Soy ever and while I can't compare it to other places yet..the only thing I can suggest is GO FOR IT! We had the one with fried pork and sausage and we are speachless.

This is a good bowl of Khao Soi. I got the beef and my girlfriend ordered the chicken curry. We were both satisfied with our meals. We did have to wait around 10 minutes to be sat on a Sunday. Fair price for the food.
Food is good, portions barely fair, but service is terrible, too much wait and it wasn't even crowded, they forgot my dessert so i had to remind them 25 minutes later, and lastly my glass was dirty
Food just looked good. There are more better price and better taste food in this area
My favorite khao soi ever! Super bowl was indeed super!! I will be back. (Come early, it gets busy!)

My family and I visited there and did not see anything special there. The Tom yum khom I had was not delicious. Spicy sausage was not tasty as well as the rice noodle. We paid over 1800 Bath and nothing goodÿå while we had much delicious meal elsewhere for 600/700. We had a better Tom yum and many different things in small shops in the village where we stay. We did not like it at all. We will never go there again and will never recommend it to anyone else at all.
The noodle is as good as my last year visit. The beef khao soy noodle is the best in town for me

Overrated. The Khao Soi portion was so tiny, I thought they forgot to add broth actually. Too expensive considering the tiny size. It was tasty though, but no difference to any street vendor. Waiter was rude and pretended to not understand when I asked if it's prepared with MSG and just left.

Arrived to a deli style number queue system, missed our number by 1 so had to requeue. Known for kai Sao was pretty basic light on flavour, pork stew was devoid of pork and beef dish was topside and not succulent as the menu suggested, dry and tough worst dish I've had in thailand.
Cool place food was good and reasonably priced. Would recommend. It is a unique way to get serviced and was kind of confusing.
Excellent food and trained staffs Very good service! Must visit place in Chiang Mai.
Must try the curry chicken leg noodle. Roselle juice is fresh and good too.

Khao Soi is delicious! They have seafood variation, and noodles boiled in normal water (without pork or chicken fat), which is important for me. Costs 60-90 thb (2020 update 85-180 thb, seafood 129). Savory kao soy with soup base thats aromatic and not too thick to slurp. Highly recommend to add other meat topping into your kao soy dish esp Chicken!!!!!
Awesome restaurant. Their specialty, kao soy, is delicious, but they also have a fun of other stuff. Try the coconut for drink/dessert.

Be careful! We had really bad food poisoning from here. I would not recommend coming here for that reason. I'm sharing this to prevent people from experiencing what we had experienced with food poisoning.
Not as nice as the vegetarian cow soi I got somewhere in Chiang Rai, but not bad. Be careful of the beverages in silver containers as some of them taste very healthy.
This place makes me want to go back to my reviews of other restaurants and remove a star. That's how good this place is.
Really nice atmosphere and lovely food, with helpful and kind staff and don't forget to pick up donuts from shop next door, soft and fluffy.
The overall flavor is good! I love this khao Soi soup!

Honestly... overrated. Wannabe posh place but the food is mediocre and not worth the price. Would not recommend it for vegetarian or vegan as the broth is chicken based. This kinda defeats the purpose of offering mushroom and egg khao soi. We wanted to try the desserts but had to leave as the amount of mosquitos in the outside area was overwhelming. Not worth it.
Very nice service , very good taste , super quality , very nice ambiance, reasonable price , excellent ! Definitely recommend
Delicious khao soi and other dishes too! You won‚Äôt be disappointed. But be prepared to wait if you arrive during peak hours.
You have to get the queue number for reservation. Despite some queue, the food is quick and yummy. Nice decorated restaurant. ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê 195 Big Bowl Mixed Khao Soi
Authentic and delicious Kao Soy. Lots of options to choose from. Very popular but not long wait.

They charge for limes, etc. That should tell you the kind of place this is. 155 baht for the small beef khao soi. Mushy noodles, very little curry/gravy. The very best Khao Soi I've tried in Chiang Mai. This place is very popular and not that large so get here early.
The Kao soi here is incredible! Quick service, delicious food, nice atmosphere. Much recommended

The food is good, but I wouldn't say it's worth the price. I had the kao soi with sausage, and sure it was good, but expensive and I was still hungry after. Amazing food and totally worth the ratings and the Michelin recognition
Value for money, and a great place to relax and enjoy the authentic Northern Thai Cuisine.
Khao Soi tastes really good. They‚Äôre fast in serving and cooking. Khao Soi costs around 69-89 baht, depends on what menu do you order.
The kao soy is good here, but not necessarily worth the wait. The amount of broth in the bowl was not sufficient but the flavour was good.

I had a very tasty Khao Soi with Thai sausage (but they have about 10 different variations, both veggie and with meat) and some shrimp tempura. This seems to be a social Media made hot Spot! Food is Dissapointing! I had a much better Koa Soy in a local shop the other day for half the Price. I had it with beef5, which was mainly fat. Nothing special at all but random Koi Soy dish. Service is quick, because there are many people.

Unforgettable experience! The service, the smiling faces in the kitchen! You‚Äôll wait in line probably for 5-10 mins, but be patient cuz good things come to those who wait! xxx

I‚Äôm not sure why there were so many good reviews of the Khao Soi. The dish was tasteless, small, had no vegetables, and very little chicken. There is MUCH, MUCH better Khao Soi available in the old city area of Chiang Mai. The pork dish was okay, as were the vegetables. The service was attentive.
Good quality northern food. Fast service. Have returned many times when in Chiangmai.
My local Chiang Mai guide brought me here for lunch and it was excellent food and service.

Very delicious. I've ordered ~ 10 times now - always Khao Soi with Chicken + 1 Chicken thigh. Price is around ‡∏ø140 including delivery in the area. Sometimes Grab offers promotions. Visited this spot twice over my stay in Chiang Mai. Great Northern Thai food and a good price. Very relaxed. My favourite restaurant in Chiang Mai (want to just keep going back here).

This restaurant was recommended to me by a Thai friend when I wanted to taste authentic flavours in a luxury setting and they delivered! Everything about the experience was amazing. Service is great. Lots of different places where you can sit. The highlight for me was definitely getting the coconut water in a steel bowl that just looked so beautiful. My noodles were delicious. Worth a visit good food not less than 200 baht per person
I love Khao Soi and the beef version here is the best I have had. A must try in Chiang Mai.

OK food. Long queue with lots of tourist. Kao soy soup is too little.

After all the fanfare about this place, I was disappointed - I ordered the signature chicken dish. There were not much in the way of noodles, seemed there were more of the crunchy ones on top. The chicken drumstick was fine. I have had better soup in food courts to be honest.
Great food, the local versions are amazing and the dishes were prepared very fast. If you want to eat for 1-2 hours, that‚Äôs the Restaurante you were looking for. Enjoy especially the Khao Soi!
Tried big bowl Kao Soy and seafood one. Good ambience and seating.
Best Kao Soi I have ever had. I recommend the super bowl which is their signature dish.
Food (khao soi) was decent, but the service was indifferent at best. They brought us the food then immediately demanded that we pay, and were quite rude about it.

Food was good, location beautiful, very busy
Taste great. Taste very clean/modern, for some Thais it might just feel like it‚Äôs missing something (due it the taste being so ‚Äòclean‚Äô)

A Michelin-guide restaurant but found the food only very average. We waited roughly 30mins for an early dinner but by the time we left, wait time was an hour. In my opinion, the food is decent but not worth the wait.
Not bad.. but not Good. Just the basics and necessary, I think there are better options around
Nice place for dinner and hangout on bars, few bars around the area.

It's reputation is better than the service. Went last year and was impressed. We were a group of 4. They forgot my drink, my partner's satay arrived after the others finished their meals, and we watched one of the cooks clean her ears then serving food (no hygienic gloves). Definitely won't be going back.
Best kao soy in town We loved sausage üòã

The Khao Soi is nice. Other food is ok. But the service is terrible. This place closes at 21:00, but the waiters are reluctant to serve since 20:30. We pushed the calling bell for several times and no one responded. One of the waiter just held the bill and standed next to our table before we even finished. The waiter took order took the wrong order and refused to apologize for it. When we argued with him, he asked ‚Äúdo you want me to pay for it?‚Äù
Nice ambient and cute drinks! Kao soy was really flavoursome! Highly recommended!
A great food place in Nimman. Good original northern food.
Went here several times bc of the kao soy! Absolutely delicious together with all the other dishes. Kao soy with soft shell crab was my favourite

Fair prices. Good food. Fast service. Lots of customers. The Kao Soy comes extremely fast but you will wait on other foods to be delivered. Was given an incorrect bill probably due to the high amount of customers. So check your bill for proper charges!

Came here for lunch on our last day in Chiang Mai. Wow. Well organized table service with a line out front. Meal came quickly. Exceptional quality. Must visit. On the Michelin list for a reason. I wish I had ordered two bowls and not because the portions were small. Just sorry the meal had to end.

I didn't have to wait long since I was number one in line, but compared to other famous restaurants, the food came out slowly. The broth was lukewarm and the noodles were undercooked... I don't think I'll be back for a second time.
Many people is in queue. Curry mee taste is good. Worth to eat here.
Love their Kao Soy, they have an extensive menu, but I can't resist traditional Kao Soy with beef.
Overall good Khao Soi, lots of tourists and the location make the price higher others.
One of the best kao soi in CNX.
Khao Soy is okey, but other deep fried dishes aint good... a little bit too dried
Must try west Thai cuisine, chicken curry noodle.
A very nice and reasonable price. Always crowded but didn‚Äôt wait that long. Variation of Khao Soi to enjoy.

the one that still open in the night to eat khao soi, the khao soi soup just like curry, but very delicious! the beef also so tender, its proved the chicken satay, must eat with the sauce because the sauce is sweet n sour will balance the taste. the spring roll just so so. but the outdoor one is too dark, better if there are more lights.
You would never find this place in Chaing Mai. But a local hot spot for sure. Lots of young folks. Unlike myself
Everything we ordered was good. Service was good as well.

I like the place, I like the food. We went twice. I didn‚Äôt like the beef so much, it was weird texture (western taste) üòâ the chicken was better My bf took the chicken satay. Delish!! Perfectly cooked and juicy and the pork curry, the sauce is very good. Sometimes there is a line sometimes not. The place is cute, but you don‚Äôt go there for the ambiance! Fast lunch or dinner. Service is fast and ok.
Excellent Kao soy. They have a ton of different Kao soy options.

Kao Soy was delicious but the service was horrible. Nothing on the menu was available except for the kao soy, so that was really annoying. They said we could get dessert but then never brought it. We asked where our dessert was and they said kitchen was closed. No variety in drinks. They took so long to take our order.
Nice atmosphere, great service, average food.

2 of us ate here on the 18-01-2024. We were told to choose a table and we sat down just before 8pm. We rang the service bell to place our order. We ordered nam prik het gap pak (not the actual name of the dish but I'm farang) along with one steamed rice. The order arrived a nice selection of vegetables but they were limp and tasteless where they had been cooked to long and they werent seasoned. The dip was OK but didn't taste fresh and was not very spicy. The waiting staff bought sticky rice first of all when we ordered steamed so we sent it back, then they bought out to 2 steamed rice where we ordered one so we sent one back. At 8.15 we were told that the restaurant was closing and we should order now if we wanted anything else, the restaurant advertises that it closes at 9pm,, customers continued to come in for a further 25 minutes and were given tables (reluctantly) at this.point we decided to ask for the bill, 15 minutes later the bill had not arrived so we asked again, a further 5 minutes and the bill arrived. I put cash in the holder and waited and 10 minutes later we called someone over and paid our bill. Nobody was overseeing the lazy waiters all of them young men. This is the first time.i have not left a tip in Thailand. I was recommended the khao soi here so I will go back band try it but if then owners are reading this they need to address the experience before more negative reviews roll in. The spicy sausage was very nice.

When you have the best khao soi ever, you can treat customers however you want. When you‚Äôre just another place among many with decent khao soi you might want to treat them like you appreciate them. Instead this is a get you in/get you out food mill with zero customer service. PLENTY of places in Chiang Mai with good khao soi who appreciate your business.

Food was nice. Tried to order dessert 30 minutes before they closed but the guy ignored us and then they said no for some reason? Then we tried to pay, and they refused our card even though the people behind us paid with card. So I had to get a Grab back to our hotel to get cash, and they didn't even apologise for the inconvenience. I think they only wanted to accept cash so that they could pocket it.
Plain tatse if u want to eat Khao Soi local restaurants is better
Large menu here not just for kao soy noodles. Good food here
Delicious but pricey üí∞

We went here around lunch-time just because it was the closest by place that did kao soy. It was our first time trying kao soy, so I can't tell if it's authentic but it's good. Crispy noodles on top and a slightly spicy curry sauce.
The service is fast and the khao soi, delicious!

Would absolutely recommend this spot if you‚Äôre visiting and want to try some excellent Kao Soy. Both the meat and vegetarian noodles were excellent and the setting is great. As an added bonus it‚Äôs a fun neighborhood to explore and worth visiting if you‚Äôve only explored the old city.

We ordered Kao Soi and Tom Yum for take away. The noodles were fine, but the soup....was just full of small lemongrass or ginger pieces, so it was impossible to eat without picking smth out of every spoon. It was my first experience ordering something at a restaurant and not at food stall and to be honest I was disappointed :(
Nice curry and authentic food

The best thing about this place is the lively, breezy space. The khao Soi was good but nothing special, the green curry had barely any chicken; had more blood cubes which wasn‚Äôt at all disclosed in the description so you had to know that was what it was in the photo. The mushroom dip with veggies was only ok. The veggies seemed boiled. The beef skewers were terrible - more fat than meat. Used to be our go to for Khao Soi. Our Khao Soi on our last visit slopped together my beef Khao Soi looked more like tiny slivers of shredded beef. Will try again at a later date.
we found two hairs in noodle local food restaurant is better than kao soi noodle the manager didn't say sorry I don't know how it got Michelin awards lol~ owner should be more care about store hygine

Liked the flavor but my Kai soy was served Luke warm and the chicken leg ice cold. Sent it back and they nukes it but still came back cold. They seem too busy to really care Great price and cute place though closes kinda early
Good taste of noodle even the mango sticky rice‚ò∫Ô∏è
Very tasty Northern Thai restaurant. Although catered towards tourists, still very authentic taste!
Great vibe, cool Nimman location and of course, yummy Khao Soi. Be sure to check out other items on the menu too, like the really good eggplant salad!

This isn‚Äôt the best khao soi I‚Äôve ever eaten. It‚Äôs good though. I had beef khao soi and the broth is delicious. The accompanying onions and pickles were delicious. The beef was really tough though. I still think this is worthy of 5 stars, though because the service was fantastic. The waiters are on it. They were really helpful and the food comes out very quickly.
Very flavorful food. Meat was soft and juicy. Great value! Ambience is very chill and relaxing.

We went based on the positive reviews. The atmosphere is pleasant, and the service is pretty good. Prices are fair and the food is OK. I had the "Super Khao Soy" and my wife had a pork noodle soup. We shared a fried spring roll appetizer. One big upside is that they actually delivered the appetizer first which is unusual for here. The downside is the spring rolls were a bit oily, but they were quite crispy. We thought this place was OK, but not a favorite here.

Our last restaurant when being in Chang Mai.... And we simply LOVED IT! I've read and also hears that it was built for tourists and so on... But I definitely don't understand why. True, the decor / atmosphere is definitely well done and modern and you see many foreigners eating there.... But there were also a lot of local and.... Being with a local... The dishes we ordered were Thai and from the region ( dishes you could any found in the Chang Mai region). Taking about the food, we did enjoy is sooo much ! It was truly good and tasty. The service was excellent üëåüëç and fast! The garden atmosphere brings a lot and we found it cosy and quiet. We ordered a lot to be honest and we were starving but also enjoying... And when the bill came... We were shocked how so NOT EXPENSIVE it was! 850 TBH for 10 dishes plus drinks plus deserts.... is definitely more that reasonable! We can only recommend this place! Worth it üôÇ

We came across this restaurant while strolling the area. We came in because of the nice atmosphere, lots of coverage and greenery. Fortunately we came at a time where there was no wait. While we were waiting for our food, people waited. But they waited under an umbrella for max 10 minutes. There is indoor seating and outdoor (covered) seating. My husband ordered the Khao with Thai sausage, which was tasty. I ordered a Northern style curry with pork (very tender. But they had small pieces of bone, which I found annoying to bit around) with jackfruit. It wasn't a coconut milk curry, so don't expect it to be creamy. This dish wasn't my first pick, I would have preferred the hung-le pork curry. But after I placed my order, they told me they didn't have it. I would expect a twice nominated Michelin star restaurant, they would know what they have in stock before people place their order. To drink we had the roselle juice and butterfly pea flower with lime juice. Both were very delicious and served with shiny silver cups. We enjoyed our time here but it would have been better had I gotten the dish I wanted in the first place.
Not worth the price.
DONT COME!!!!! tourist trap. long wait, high price, low quality food, eat at khao soi lung prakit kat kom instead, you can get 3x the food for the same price, and infinitely better quality

Unfair to rate as they don't provide for vegetarian or vegan options. Service was quick though. English speaking waitress attended. Popular though and would recommend you check it out if diet ü•¶üçéü•óüçåis not fussy like mine. üôèüòâ
Awesome Khao Soi. Great service. Will go back to try some of the other menu options
Definitely one of the best places in Thailand for a foodie. A must-visit

Kao Soy is a very local Chiang Mai dish. They are served in several flavours. Don't miss out tasting them if you can. This cozy restaurant serves good kao soy. Stumbled upon this Michelin-starred eatery by accident while looking to visit another renowned restaurant in Chiangmai (not knowing that other place was a reservation only venue), and settled for lunch here. The queue was really long even at 2pm, but the turnover was quick enough to get us a table within 10 minutes, aided by their expansion to a neighbouring shophouse's yard. We had a big khao soi that had a bit of everything in it and a standard bowl of beef khao soi, an extremely crispy fried egg with minced pork (wanted to try the ant eggs but the wife declined), and another bowl of soupy bamboo shoots with meat in it. As most of the food in the extensive menu (including a more exotic bamboo worms) were spicy, they provided a free plate of fried rice for our young daughter. To beat the heat, we ordered an interesting globe of dehusked coconut flesh with the juice in it, an iced chrysanthemum drink complete with a decorative flower, and a dessert reminiscent of chendol from Singapore and Malaysia. All in all, the food was pretty good, though it must be said that khao soi being a curry based staple dish in Chiangmai, is not necessarily for everyone.
Wow. The Kao Soy ( Type of Northern Thai Soup) was so good. Delicious. Michelin Recognized place. And you can see why. The food tastes good.

Delicious Kao Soy, and the vegetarian version with gorgeous mushrooms! There is a vegetarian option for many (if not most) of the menu categories. When we arrived, there were six groups ahead of us but because they are so organized here, we didn‚Äôt wait long at all for a table at lunchtime.

Atmosphere is nice However the quality of food is pretty bad, stir fried pork with vegetables has strong smell Fish on the Bamboo shoot soup aren't fresh Asked for a fork but never delivered. Very disappointed Paired over 600 for 3 ppl Won't come back for sure

The star of the menu at Kao Soy Nimman is their signature dish, Kao Soy. This traditional Northern Thai curry noodle soup is bursting with flavors, combining tender chicken or beef with a rich and fragrant curry broth. The addition of crispy egg noodles on top adds a delightful crunch to each spoonful. Apart from Kao Soy, the restaurant offers a variety of other Northern Thai specialties that are equally mouthwatering. From flavorful larb salads to aromatic gaeng hang lay curry, each dish showcases the unique blend of spices and herbs that are characteristic of Northern Thai cuisine. Whether you're a foodie looking to explore authentic Northern Thai cuisine or simply someone who appreciates good food, Kao Soy Nimman is a must-visit.

Instagram: @ol_no_nichijoramen Khao Soi Gai - 85 Baht This popular Khao Soi spot is located around the Nimmanhaemin area in Chiang Mai. It's become well-known after being featured in the Michelin Bib Gourmand list. I visited around 4 PM on a Sunday, and since I opted for the terrace seating, there was no wait. Despite Chiang Mai's 38¬∞C heat, the fans on the terrace kept things pleasantly cool. I ordered the classic chicken Khao Soi, which arrived with thick boiled noodles topped with crispy fried noodles and cilantro. A separate plate with purple onions, pickled cabbage, and lime was also provided. The soup has a coconut-based Thai curry flavor. Initially mild, it develops a delightful spicy kick as you eat, making it quite addictive. The thick noodles soak up the soup beautifully, making each bite irresistible. The crispy noodles can be enjoyed either plain or dipped in the soup, offering a nice contrast in texture. The bone-in chicken topping was tender and fell apart easily with chopsticks, making it very easy to eat. I added all the purple onions, pickled cabbage, and lime to the soup during the meal, and each addition complemented the soup perfectly, keeping it flavorful and exciting until the very end. I ended up finishing every bit of the soup!
